================================================================
SOLO BRANDS, INC. (OTCQB: SBDS)
Point of View
Fiscal Q1 2026, quarter ended March 31, 2026
(Form 10-Q, reported May 14, 2026)
================================================================

> Top-Line Performance: Net sales fell to $62.9m in Q1 FY26 from $77.3m in Q1 FY25, down (18.6%) / ($14.4m) YoY, driven by lower DTC and retail volumes and tariff pressure (Solo Stove (38.7%) to $16.0m; Chubbies (14.1%) to $36.7m). Full-year net sales were ~$316m in FY25 vs ~$455m in FY24. Management reaffirmed FY26 guidance of $280-310m net sales and $24-30m Adjusted EBITDA.

> Profitability: Gross margin contracted to 52.3% in Q1 FY26 from 55.2% in Q1 FY25, down 290 bps, on tariff costs and a heavier retail mix. Operating margin improved to (7.5%) in Q1 FY26 from (13.6%) in Q1 FY25, with operating loss of ($4.7m) vs ($10.5m), as operating expenses fell (29.3%) to $37.6m. Net loss narrowed to ($5.5m) in Q1 FY26 from ($18.6m) in Q1 FY25. For the full year, net loss was ($145.4m) in FY25 vs ($180.2m) in FY24, with Adjusted EBITDA of $18.5m vs $32.6m.

> Cash Flows: Net cash used in operating activities was ($16.1m) in Q1 FY26, a sharp improvement from ($75.2m) in Q1 FY25 as restructuring and consulting costs fell. Cash fell to $16.5m at March 31, 2026 from $20.0m at year-end 2025.

> Liquidity and debt position: Cash and equivalents were $16.5m at March 31, 2026, down from $20.0m at year-end 2025; inventory was $82.9m. Total debt principal was $273.9m ($258.9m term loan plus $15.0m revolver), much at 7-9%+ rates with PIK interest inflating balances, against $63.6m revolver availability. Stockholders' equity was $46.3m, swinging from a ($335.4m) deficit at year-end 2025 after the Corporate Simplification removed the Up-C structure.

> Working Capital: Inventory was $82.9m at March 31, 2026. The Company is pursuing ~$10m of tariff refunds; most claims are accepted but no cash has been received, leaving a key liquidity source uncertain.

> Operational Restructuring Plan: FY25 restructuring, contract-termination, and impairment charges were $93.5m. Cost actions yield ~$8m annualized payroll savings plus ~$3.5m operational savings; the Corporate Simplification consolidated tax filing and drove a $6.6m tax benefit.

> Going Concern: The Q1 FY26 10-Q carries an explicit going-concern statement tied to covenant compliance beginning September 30, 2026; management believes cost cuts and ~$10m of tariff refunds alleviate substantial doubt for twelve months.

> Regulatory & Delisting Overhang: NYSE suspended trading on April 22, 2025 over an "abnormally low" price and a sub-$15m market cap; the appeal failed and shares now trade on OTCQB as SBDS. A reverse stock split was contemplated.

> Management Change: Founder-CEO John Merris exited January 2024; successor Chris Metz (ex-Vista Outdoor) resigned February 2025 after ~13 months; board member John Larson has served as interim CEO since, signaling sustained leadership instability.

> Delayed SEC filing: Not flagged. FY25 results on March 19, 2026 and Q1 FY26 results on May 14, 2026 were filed on schedule, with no Form 12b-25 extension reported.

